Message-ID: <GV0P278MB0417C563FD8C87F5CE31950DECBA2@GV0P278MB0417.CHEP278.PROD.OUTLOOK.COM>

Bill,

Apple does not support OpenMP in their toolchain, and OpenMP is disabled in XCode. Simon and others rely on the fact that the toolchain is built on top of Clang and thus the OpenMP support can be patched in. However, as far as Apple goes all this is undocumented behavior and subject to change at any time. So I wouldn?t expect things improving any time soon.

Best,

Taras

